transposed_data$Phenotype <- phenotype_labels
transposed_data <- transposed_data[, c("Phenotype", setdiff(names(transposed_data), "Phenotype"))]

The following section includes the scaling of data using Variable Stability Scaling (VAST) to stabilise the variance across variables while preserving the metabolites having higher mean intensities.

numeric_data <- transposed_data[, sapply(transposed_data, is.numeric)]
vast_scaling <- function(x) {
  variable_mean <- mean(x, na.rm = TRUE)
  variable_sd <- sd(x, na.rm = TRUE)
  ((x - variable_mean) / variable_sd) * (variable_mean / variable_sd)
}
vast_scaled_data <- as.data.frame(lapply(numeric_data, vast_scaling))
vast_scaled_data <- data.frame(Phenotype = transposed_data$Phenotype, vast_scaled_data)

Partial Least Squares Discriminant analyses (PLS-DA) and Variable of importance calculation from PLS-DA projection This section includes LIMMA Differential expression Analysis to find metabolites in comparison of 0M ERAP1 inhibitor with 10M ERAP1 inhibitor, 50M ERAP1 inhibitor treated and ERAP1 Knockout cells. Here WT_DMSO represents 0M ERAP1 inhibitor, WT_10: 10M ERAP1 inhibitor, WT_50: 50M ERAP1 inhibitor and KO repreents: ERAP1 Knockout

metabolite_data_matrix <- as.matrix(metabolite_data1)
rownames(metabolite_data_matrix) <- paste0(vast_scaled_data$Phenotype, "_", seq_len(nrow(vast_scaled_data)))

phenotype_labels <- factor(trimws(vast_scaled_data$Phenotype))
phenotype_labels <- droplevels(phenotype_labels[phenotype_labels != "CMTRX"])
keep_rows <- vast_scaled_data$Phenotype != "CMTRX"
metabolite_data_matrix <- metabolite_data_matrix[keep_rows, ]
rownames(metabolite_data_matrix) <- paste0(vast_scaled_data$Phenotype[keep_rows], "_", seq_len(sum(keep_rows)))

design <- model.matrix(~ 0 + phenotype_labels)
colnames(design) <- levels(phenotype_labels)
rownames(design) <- rownames(metabolite_data_matrix)

fit <- lmFit(t(metabolite_data_matrix), design)
contrast <- makeContrasts(KO - WT_DMSO, levels = design)
fit2 <- contrasts.fit(fit, contrast)
fit2 <- eBayes(fit2)
#FDR adjustment
p_adjusted <- p.adjust(fit2$p.value, method = "fdr")
fit2$p_adjusted <- p_adjusted
#head(fit2)
fit2_df <- data.frame(
  Metabolite = rownames(fit2$t),   
  logFC = fit2$coefficients[, 1],  
  t_stat = fit2$t[, 1],            
  p_value = fit2$p.value[, 1],     
  p_adjusted = fit2$p_adjusted,
  adj.p.value= fit2$F.p.value)
#View(fit2_df)

top_results <- topTable(fit2, number = 10)  
#print(top_results)

  geom_point(
    data = results_wt_ko[results_wt_ko$Label != "", ],
    aes(x = logFC, y = -log10(adj.P.Val)),
    color = volcano_colors["Upregulated"],
    size = 3.5
  ) +

  ) +

  labs(
    title = "ERAP1-component cells without inhibitor (control) vs ERAP1 Knockout (Positive Ionisation Mode)",

    y = "-log10(P-adjusted value)",
    color = "Significance"
  ) +
  theme_minimal(base_size = 14) +

This section includes the Boxplot analysis using ANOVA for key metabolite features to compare between conditions under study

selected_ids <- c(
  "HIMETPOSFT09948", "HIMETPOSFT08071", "HIMETPOSFT08805", "HIMETPOSFT10814",
  "HIMETPOSFT09547", "HIMETPOSFT06068", "HIMETPOSFT10197", "HIMETPOSFT06207",
  "HIMETPOSFT08949", "HIMETPOSFT10211", "HIMETPOSFT12121", "HIMETPOSFT12258",
  "HIMETPOSFT06097", "HIMETPOSFT06296", "HIMETPOSFT08263", "HIMETPOSFT04227"
)

metabolite_names <- c(
  "HIMETPOSFT09948" = "citrulline [M+H]+",
  "HIMETPOSFT08071" = "glutamine [M+H]+",
  "HIMETPOSFT08805" = "glutathione [M+H]+",
  "HIMETPOSFT10814" = "glutathione disulfide [M+H]+",
  "HIMETPOSFT09547" = "histidine [M+H]+",
  "HIMETPOSFT06068" = "isoleucine/leucine [M+H]+",
  "HIMETPOSFT10197" = "lysine [M+H]+",
  "HIMETPOSFT06207" = "phenylalanine [M+H]+",
  "HIMETPOSFT08949" = "phosphocholine [M+H]+",
  "HIMETPOSFT10211" = "S-adenosyl-L-methionine [M]+",
  "HIMETPOSFT12121" = "spermidine [M+H]+",
  "HIMETPOSFT12258" = "spermine [M+H]+",
  "HIMETPOSFT06097" = "sphingosine 1-phosphate [M+H]+",
  "HIMETPOSFT06296" = "tryptophan [M-NH2+H]+",
  "HIMETPOSFT08263" = "tyrosine [M+H]+",
  "HIMETPOSFT04227" = "choline [M]+"
)
filtered_data1 <- complete_data %>% filter(id %in% selected_ids)
#head(filtered_data1)
long_df <- filtered_data1 %>%
  pivot_longer(cols = -id, names_to = "Sample", values_to = "Concentration") %>%
  mutate(
    Condition = case_when(
      str_detect(Sample, "WT_DMSO") ~ "0M ERAP1 inhibitor",
      str_detect(Sample, "WT_10uM") ~ "10M ERAP1 inhibitor",
      str_detect(Sample, "WT_50uM") ~ "50M ERAP1 inhibitor",
      str_detect(Sample, "KO") ~ "KO",
      TRUE ~ NA_character_
    ),
    Concentration = as.numeric(Concentration),
    Concentration = log10(Concentration + 1),
    FacetLabel = metabolite_names[id]
  ) %>%
  filter(!is.na(Condition) & !is.na(FacetLabel))

g <- ggplot(long_df, aes(x = Condition, y = Concentration, color = Condition)) +
  geom_boxplot(outlier.shape = NA, size = 1.5, color = "black", fill = NA) +
  geom_jitter(width = 0.2, alpha = 0.8, size = 3, shape = 16, show.legend = TRUE) +
  stat_compare_means(
    method = "anova",
    label = "p.format",
    label.y.npc = 0.95,
    size = 4,
    fontface = "bold",
    color = "black"
  ) +
  scale_color_manual(values = boxplot_colors) +
  facet_wrap(~ FacetLabel, scales = "free_y", nrow = 4, ncol = 5) +
  labs(
    x = NULL,
    y = expression(log[10]*"(Mol + 1)"),
    color = "Condition"
  ) +
  guides(color = guide_legend(override.aes = list(size = 5))) +
  theme_pubr(base_size = 18) +
  theme(
    legend.position = "bottom",
    legend.text = element_text(size = 12, face = "bold"),
    legend.title = element_text(size = 13, face = "bold"),
    legend.key.size = unit(1.5, "lines"),
    strip.text = element_text(face = "bold", color = "black", size = 12),
    strip.background = element_blank(),
    axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 90, hjust = 1, size = 10, face = "bold"),
    axis.text.y = element_text(size = 10, face = "bold"),
    axis.title.y = element_text(size = 14, face = "bold"),
    axis.title.x = element_text(margin = margin(t = 10), face = "bold"),
    panel.spacing = unit(1.5, "lines"),
    plot.margin = margin(12, 12, 12, 12),
    panel.border = element_rect(color = "black", linewidth = 1.2, fill = NA),
    axis.line = element_line(color = "black", linewidth = 1.2)
  )
g
